@node part4 "How to use the program"

            Run it and it will display a message in a requester.

            Click on 'OK' and the program will end.

            Clicking 'About' will display information about the program.


            Note: It is quite easy to add futher quotes:
            Load the 'quotes.data' file in a text editor and just type
            more text. One quote is TWO lines of text. I would appreciate
            it if you make sure that there isn't a blank line at the end
            of the file as it will confuse the program.

            *** Do not change or delete the word 'sayings' at the top
            of the file - this is used by the program to identify the file. ***

            Each line is limited to 254 characters in length.
            The maximum number of quotes that the program can handle is 100
            - more than this may cause the program either to crash or fail
            unexpectedly.


                        @{"Return to contents" link main}
@endnode

